title: [Cysaegir, Copse]
description: Larkspurs, violets, alyssums, and bluebells thrive here by a gurgling brook.  Offering shades of yellow, blue, pink, and purple, their raceme clusters face the sun, and seem to quiver in excitement whenever a soft breeze sweeps across the ground.  Some spiraling stairs twine around a bole and lead to a shop built mid-level on the massive tree.  An exceptionally over-sized branch droops low offering shade and relaxation beside a whitewashed cottage.  Securely strung up between the trees are well-made hammocks, constructed from woven vines.
